 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Patent Associate Attorney- Entry Level Hanley Flight & Zimmerman Chicago, IL 60606 Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Our Chicago boutique patent law firm is in search of 3L students (4L night program) in their final year of legal study to join our patent prosecution team. HFZ represents clients in a wide variety of industries and technologies including the automotive, aerospace, electronics, software, Internet, e-commerce, wireless and cloud technology sectors, artificial intelligence and machine learning, biomedical instrumentation and consumer goods, process technologies and digital signal processing industries, media and process control technologies, amongst others. This full-time position has a billable hour requirement of 1850 hours with a year-end bonus potential. 
 
 
 
 How to Apply 
 
 Please apply for the "Patent Associate Attorney- Entry Level" position at https://hfzlaw.com/recruit 
 
 Please provide us with your resume, transcripts from both your engineering and law schools, proof of passing of ethics test, and a cover letter. If available, a sample of a published office action response you drafted. 
 
 Hanley, Flight & Zimmerman LLC is committed to diversity as a core value of the firm. HFZ is an Equal Opportunity/ M/F/Vet/Disabled Employer. 
 
 
 
 Requirements 
 
 Requirements 
 
 JD and Engineering Degree (Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Biomedical Engineering or Mechanical Engineering only)
 
 Available to work upon completion of Law School Program
 
 Previous law clerk/summer associate work focused primarily on drafting and prosecuting patent applications and office action responses is preferred
 
 Excellent academic credentials in undergraduate engineering program and law school
 
 Passing result on Ethics exam 
 
 
 
 
 Benefits
 Benefits 
 
 Competitive compensation commensurate with experience and strong benefits package
 
 Excellent work/life balance
 
 HFZ works with many Fortune 500 technology companies and three of the top twenty-five patent producing companies in the US
 
 Exposure to a wide variety of technologies and clients
 
 Team environment
 
 Small Firm environment with an Open-door Policy allowing easy access to senior attorneys and Managing Members
 
 Dedicated mentorship program with new attorneys matched with senior attorney or Managing Members. 
 
 Income/Capital Membership considerations based upon experience and merit, not rigid time tables. Hanley Flight & Zimmerman 9 days ago original job Report job Apply Now Apply On Company Site Save this job Save this job Patent Attorney jobs in Chicago, IL Jobs at Hanley Flight & Zimmerman in Chicago, IL Patent Attorney salaries in Chicago, IL Let employers find you Thousands of employers search for candidates on Indeed Upload your resume 
